name: Tom + Chee
directions: When you walk in the door, keep going straight to the back past the drink fountain. They are gendered single bathrooms, but hidden enough from the rest of the restaurant that no one should (hopefully) give you trouble. Locking.
comment: I don't know if you have to be a paying customer or not. The staff can't see the bathroom area well anyway though.

name: Westside Provisions District
directions:
If you enter the shopping center at the entrance between Star Provisions and Jeni's, down the hall across from the Jeni's exit is the "women's" (black door) and a little further down toward the tables is the "men's." Both are locking, with a large single locking stall within (no idea why.) 

[There are also multi-stall gendered indoor bathrooms across the bridge near Room and Board that are almost always totally empty (except on busy weekend nights), within the glass doors across from the Dtox juice stand.]
comment: These two bathrooms are gendered but people use whichever one all the time if the other is in use. I would just say wait until there isn't a line and dash inside. I work here and have never had any problems, and to my knowledge none of my trans coworkers have had problems either.

name: Kitsch'n
comment: Two gender neutral restrooms

name: Jeni's Splendid Ice Creams
directions: At the very back of the shop behind a small barrier wall. Single, locking door, sometimes has menstrual products available.
comment: Might have to be a paying customer, but really you can either just go straight back or try some free ice cream samples first if you feel you need to. There's also free water in a metal jug on the way to the bathrooms. :)

name: CCNTH
directions: In the admin office close to the center of campus, not the attendance office in the front.
comment: This used to be a staff bathroom, but now any student can use it. Always clean. Secretary is very kind and won't blink if you come in to use it. The entire staff in general is very trans friendly. Pretty easy to use this on the DL since students use the office for a myriad of things.

name: Democracy Coffee House

name: Starbucks

comment: The restrooms are gendered single stalls, however, it's a super safe place for everyone. Don't hesitate to tell any of the baristas if anyone makes you feel unsafe.
